Key Match Events: The Celtics were dominated in the second half as they lost 105-92 to the Thunder.
The Celtics mustered just 15 points in the third quarter, going 1-for-13 on 3s.
The Thunder outscored the Celtics 29-12 in the fourth quarter.
Jayson Tatum had 26 points and 10 rebounds for the Celtics.
Jaylen Brown added 21 points for the Celtics.
MVP candidate Shai Gilgeous-Alexander finished with 33 points and 11 rebounds for the Thunder.
Pre-Game Insights: The game was billed as a potential NBA Finals matchup between the West's best team and the reigning NBA champs.
Post-Match Reflections: The Celtics were an efficient machine through the first half but struggled in the second half.
The Thunder have been one of the best teams in the league thus far this season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Sunday was the first time the Celtics were at full strength with their top-8 rotation players available since Nov. 29.
